               <component>
                  <section ID="Section_6.2">
                     <id root="15f98053-b397-4f3c-8ded-aa01eb408f85"/>
                     <code code="42229-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION"/>
                     <title>
                        <content styleCode="bold">6.2 Postmarketing Experience</content>
                     </title>
                     <text>
                        <paragraph>The following adverse reactions have been identified during post-approval use of adapalene and benzoyl peroxide gel 0.1% / 2.5%: eyelid edema, sunburn, blister, pain of skin, pruritus, swelling face, conjunctivitis, skin discoloration, rash, eczema, throat tightness and allergic contact dermatitis. Because these reactions are reported voluntarily from a population of uncertain size, it is not always possible to reliably estimate their frequency or establish a causal relationship to drug exposure.</paragraph>
                     </text>
                     <effectiveTime value="20260615"/>
                  </section>
